This could happen for many reasons. Windows does not allow the deletion of a 
file that is open by an application, for instance. The workaround is to 
perform the operation again. The only action that we would take is to correct 
poor error reporting or if the above stated workaround (for windows behavior) 
didn't work. Please reopen if you feel that error handling was not not 
adequate or the stated workaround does not work.
